Program: Discovery
Title: 05/12/2011 GMT
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00lw94w
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 12 Dec 2011
When leptin failed to be a wonder solution to obesity, this hormone produced by fat cells, disappeared from the headlines. Twenty years on scientists now believe leptin is critical to how the body works, regulating appetite, the immune response, inflammation and depression. Vivienne Parry investigates. Show less